main event: Radar tracking and visual observation of unidentified objects over multiple locations in July 1965.
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar for 27 minutes and involved military personnel., The sighting involved 1-2 objects that were possibly high-altitude balloons., There were reports of visual sightings aligning with radar targets., Military aircraft were vectored in to intercept the radar targets, but no visual contact was made., The analysis concluded that the objects seen were likely balloons launched prior to the radar sightings.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects detected on radar
location: Eastmont, Oakdale, Bellefontaine, Findlay, Stubenville, Ohio, USA
witness description: Mrs. [redacted], a 35-year-old housewife from Pittsburgh, observed along with her two children.
